This project builds on court data from CourtListener, a project of the Free Law
Project (https://free.law/, https://www.courtlistener.com/), via the CourtListener
REST API and the quarterly bulk-data exports.

The underlying U.S. federal court opinions and docket records are public records of
the U.S. federal courts. CourtListener's own content is licensed under a Creative
Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-ND 4.0) license, except
where indicated. Use of CourtListener data is governed by CourtListener's terms:
https://www.courtlistener.com/terms/

A great deal of this project rests on the Free Law Project's work; please review and
support it. See docs/data-sources.md for how this project sources, redistributes,
and handles personal data in those records.

FedCourtsAI is independent and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Free Law
Project or any court. The predictions and evaluations in this repository are
model-generated and are not official court records.
